# Styling Standards

## SCSS Module Structure

### File Naming
- **Component styles**: Use `ComponentName.module.scss` for component-specific styles
- **Global styles**: Place in `src/assets/scss/` (e.g., `global.scss`, `variables.scss`)
- **Import in component**: `import styles from './styles.module.scss'`

### Class Naming
- **camelCase**: Use camelCase for class names (e.g., `button`, `iconButton`, `block`)
- **Component prefix**: Not required, but can be used for clarity
- **BEM alternative**: Can use BEM-like naming if preferred (e.g., `button--primary`)

## SCSS File Structure

### Component SCSS Module
```scss
// Button/styles.module.scss
@use "./global.scss" as *;
@use "@/assets/scss/variables" as *;

.button {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
  font-size: map-get($font-sizes, md);
  font-weight: map-get($font-weights, medium);
  line-height: 1.5;
  cursor: pointer;
  user-select: none;
  border-radius: map-get($border-radii, md);
  transition: all 0.15s ease-in-out;
  gap: map-get($spacers, 1);

  // State styles
  &:hover {
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  &:focus {
    outline: 0;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 0.25rem
      color-mix(in srgb, var(--bs-primary) 35%, transparent);
  }

  &:disabled {
    opacity: 0.65;
    pointer-events: none;
    cursor: not-allowed;
  }

  // Variant styles (if using data attributes or classes)
  &.primary {
    background: var(--bs-primary);
    color: #fff;
  }

  &.secondary {
    background: var(--bs-secondary);
    color: #fff;
  }

  // Size styles
  &.small {
    padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
    font-size: map-get($font-sizes, sm);
  }

  &.large {
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    font-size: map-get($font-sizes, lg);
  }

  // Modifier classes
  &.block {
    width: 100%;
    display: flex;
  }

  &.iconButton {
    padding: 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  // Responsive styles
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    font-size: map-get($font-sizes, sm);
    padding: 0.375rem 0.75rem;
  }
}
```

### Global SCSS Variables

Global variables are defined in `src/assets/scss/_variables.scss`:

```scss
// src/assets/scss/_variables.scss
// Font sizes
$font-sizes: (
  xs: 0.75rem,
  sm: 0.875rem,
  md: 1rem,
  lg: 1.125rem,
  xl: 1.25rem,
);

// Font weights
$font-weights: (
  light: 300,
  normal: 400,
  medium: 500,
  semibold: 600,
  bold: 700,
);

// Spacing
$spacers: (
  0: 0,
  1: 0.25rem,
  2: 0.5rem,
  3: 1rem,
  4: 1.5rem,
  5: 3rem,
);

// Border radius
$border-radii: (
  sm: 0.25rem,
  md: 0.375rem,
  lg: 0.5rem,
  xl: 1rem,
  round: 50%,
);
```

## Bootstrap Integration

### CSS Variables
Bootstrap 5 provides CSS variables that can be used:

```scss
.button {
  background-color: var(--bs-primary);
  color: var(--bs-white);
  border-color: var(--bs-primary);
  
  &:hover {
    background-color: var(--bs-primary-dark);
  }
}
```

### Utility Classes
Use Bootstrap utility classes in JSX when appropriate:

```typescript
<div className="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mb-3">
  <h2 className="mb-0">Title</h2>
  <Button variant="primary">Action</Button>
</div>
```

### React Bootstrap Components
Leverage React Bootstrap components and extend with custom styles:

```typescript
import { Button as BootstrapButton } from 'react-bootstrap';
import styles from './Button.module.scss';

<BootstrapButton
  variant="primary"
  className={styles.button}
>
  Click me
</BootstrapButton>
```

## SCSS Module Usage in Components

```typescript
import React from 'react';
import styles from './Button.module.scss';
import classnames from 'classnames';

const Button: React.FC<ButtonProps> = ({ variant, className, children }) => {
  const buttonClasses = classnames(
    styles.button,
    variant && styles[variant],
    className
  );

  return (
    <button className={buttonClasses}>
      {children}
    </button>
  );
};
```

## Theme-Aware Styling

### Using Bootstrap CSS Variables

**Always use Bootstrap CSS variables for theme-aware colors:**

```scss
// ComponentName.module.scss
@use "@/assets/scss/variables.scss" as *;

.component {
  // ✅ Use CSS variables for theme-aware colors
  background: var(--bs-body-bg); // Auto-switches with theme
  color: var(--bs-body-color); // Auto-switches with theme
  border: 1px solid var(--bs-border-color); // Auto-switches with theme
  
  // ✅ Use SCSS variables for static values
  padding: map-get($spacers, 2);
  border-radius: map-get($border-radii, md);
  
  &:hover {
    background-color: rgba(
      var(--bs-primary-rgb, 0, 0, 0),
      0.1
    ); // Uses primary color with transparency
  }
}
```

### Theme-Aware Color Variables

**Available Bootstrap CSS variables:**
- `var(--bs-body-bg)` - Background color (auto-switches)
- `var(--bs-body-color)` - Text color (auto-switches)
- `var(--bs-border-color)` - Border color (auto-switches)
- `var(--bs-primary)` - Primary color
- `var(--bs-secondary)` - Secondary color
- `var(--bs-success)`, `var(--bs-warning)`, `var(--bs-danger)`, `var(--bs-info)`
- `var(--bs-primary-rgb)` - RGB values for transparency

**See [theme-system.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/theme-system.mdc) for complete theme system documentation.**

## Responsive Design

### Mobile-First Approach
Start with mobile styles, then add desktop styles:

```scss
.component {
  // Mobile styles (default)
  padding: 1rem;
  font-size: 0.875rem;

  // Tablet and up
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  // Desktop and up
  @media (min-width: 992px) {
    padding: 2rem;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
  }
}
```

### Bootstrap Breakpoints
Use Bootstrap breakpoints for consistency:

```scss
// Bootstrap breakpoints
$grid-breakpoints: (
  xs: 0,
  sm: 576px,
  md: 768px,
  lg: 992px,
  xl: 1200px,
  xxl: 1400px,
);

// Usage
@media (min-width: map-get($grid-breakpoints, md)) {
  // Styles for md and up
}
```

## Global Styles

Global styles are in `src/assets/scss/`:

- **`_variables.scss`**: SCSS variables (colors, spacing, typography)
- **`mixins.scss`**: Reusable SCSS mixins
- **`global.scss`**: Global styles and resets
- **`admin.scss`**: Admin-specific global styles
- **`bootstrap-custom.scss`**: Bootstrap customizations
- **`colors.scss`**: Color definitions
- **`main.scss`**: Main SCSS entry point

Import global variables in component SCSS:

```scss
@use "./global.scss" as *;
@use "@/assets/scss/variables" as *;
```

## Accessibility

### Color Contrast
- **Text**: Ensure sufficient contrast (WCAG AA: 4.5:1 for normal text)
- **Interactive elements**: Clear visual feedback on hover/focus

### Focus Indicators
```scss
.button {
  &:focus {
    outline: 0;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 0.25rem
      color-mix(in srgb, var(--bs-primary) 35%, transparent);
  }
  
  &:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--bs-primary);
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }
}
```

### Reduced Motion
```scss
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  * {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    animation-iteration-count: 1 !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```

## Performance Best Practices

- **CSS Modules**: Use for component-scoped styles (prevents style conflicts)
- **Avoid inline styles**: Use CSS modules or utility classes instead
- **Minimize specificity**: Keep selectors simple and specific
- **Use CSS variables**: For theming and dynamic values
- **Optimize imports**: Only import what you need from global SCSS files

## Class Name Utilities

Use `classnames` or `clsx` for conditional class names:

```typescript
import classnames from 'classnames';

const buttonClasses = classnames(
  styles.button,
  {
    [styles.primary]: variant === 'primary',
    [styles.disabled]: disabled,
    [styles.loading]: loading,
  },
  className
);
```

## SCSS Best Practices

1. ✅ Use SCSS modules for component styles
2. ✅ Import global variables using `@use`
3. ✅ Use camelCase for class names
4. ✅ **CRITICAL: Use Bootstrap CSS variables** (`var(--bs-*)`) for ALL theme-aware colors
5. ✅ **Use SCSS variables** (`map-get($spacers, *)`) for static values (spacing, typography, border-radius)
6. ✅ Use mobile-first responsive design
7. ✅ Keep selectors simple and specific
8. ✅ **Always test components in both light and dark themes**
9. ✅ Ensure proper focus states for accessibility
10. ✅ Use `classnames` for conditional classes
11. ✅ Organize styles logically (base → states → variants → responsive)
12. ✅ Use RGB variables for transparency: `rgba(var(--bs-primary-rgb, 0, 0, 0), 0.15)`

## Theme System Integration

The application uses `next-themes` for theme management with Bootstrap CSS variables for theme-aware styling. See [theme-system.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/theme-system.mdc) for complete documentation.

### Critical Theme Rules

**✅ DO - Use CSS Variables for Theme-Aware Colors:**
```scss
// Backgrounds and text
background: var(--bs-body-bg);
color: var(--bs-body-color);
border-color: var(--bs-border-color);

// Theme colors
background-color: var(--bs-primary);
color: var(--bs-white);
border-color: var(--bs-border-color);

// Form controls
background-color: var(--bs-input-bg);
color: var(--bs-input-color);
border-color: var(--bs-input-border-color);
```

**❌ DON'T - Use SCSS Variables for Theme Colors:**
```scss
// ❌ These won't switch with theme
background-color: $body-bg;
color: $body-color;
background-color: map-get($theme-colors, light);
color: $body-color;
```

**✅ DO - Use SCSS Variables for Static Values:**
```scss
// Spacing, typography, border-radius (these don't need theme switching)
padding: map-get($spacers, 2);
font-size: map-get($font-sizes, md);
border-radius: map-get($border-radii, md);
```

### Common Theme-Aware Patterns

```scss
// Component with theme-aware styling
.component {
  // Theme-aware colors
  background: var(--bs-body-bg);
  color: var(--bs-body-color);
  border: 1px solid var(--bs-border-color);
  
  // Static values
  padding: map-get($spacers, 2);
  border-radius: map-get($border-radii, md);
  
  // Hover with transparency
  &:hover {
    background-color: rgba(
      var(--bs-primary-rgb, 0, 0, 0),
      0.1
    );
  }
  
  // Active state
  &.active {
    background-color: rgba(
      var(--bs-primary-rgb, 0, 0, 0),
      0.15
    );
    color: var(--bs-primary);
  }
}
```

### Migration Guide

If you find components using SCSS variables for theme colors, migrate them:

```scss
// ❌ Before (not theme-aware)
.component {
  background-color: $body-bg;
  color: $body-color;
  background-color: map-get($theme-colors, light);
}

// ✅ After (theme-aware)
.component {
  background: var(--bs-body-bg);
  color: var(--bs-body-color);
  background-color: var(--bs-body-bg);
}
```
